Sentencas: Finding suitable cathode materials is the key to developing intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: A novel cathode material Pr0.9Sr0.1Cr0.5Fe0.5O3-δ for intermediate temperate solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: In this work, a novel Pr0.9Sr0.1Cr0.5Fe0.5O3-delta (PSCF) is prepared by EDTA-citric acid-nitrate combustion (EDTA: Ethylenediaminetetraacetic acid).
Titulo: A novel cathode material Pr0.9Sr0.1Cr0.5Fe0.5O3-δ for intermediate temperate solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Analysis by thermogravimetry and differential scanning calorimetry techniques (TG-DSC), and X-ray diffraction (XRD) demonstrate that a structure composed by a single perovskite is obtained upon sintering in air at 950 degrees C. Brunauer-Emmett-Teller (BET) and field emission scanning electron microscopy (FESEM) were applied to analyze the physical characteristics of the cathode materials.
Titulo: A novel cathode material Pr0.9Sr0.1Cr0.5Fe0.5O3-δ for intermediate temperate solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: In addition, PSCF-GDC as a cathode and the performances of the complete cell (NiO-GDC/GDC/PSCF-GDC) at 600 degrees C - 700 degrees C are also tested when 99% H-2 and ambient air were fed into anode and cathode, respectively.
Titulo: A novel cathode material Pr0.9Sr0.1Cr0.5Fe0.5O3-δ for intermediate temperate solid oxide fuel cell
